On December 24, 2010, Assistant to the President for Counter-Terrorism and Homeland Security John Brennan held a conference call with various government officials to discuss the response to holiday threats. The call included Secretary Napolitano, DNI Clapper, FBI Director Mueller, NCTC Director Leiter, Deputy Director of the CIA Morrell, and representatives from the counter-terrorism community. They discussed the additional security measures and coordination with foreign partners to ensure vigilance during the holiday season.